news_insight_text_link.news_insight_description: Antora Energy has developed a new thermal battery with breakthrough efficiencies using heat-to-power thermophotovoltaic (TPV) technology. Additionally, the company has been selected for ARPA-E's SCALEUP funding, which aims to support gigaton-scale industrial decarbonization.

org_similarity_summary.insight_similar_orgs: Antora Energy, ZincFive, Form Energy, Powin Energy, Natron Energy, and Solid Power operate in the energy storage and battery technology sector. ZincFive, Form Energy, Powin Energy, and Natron Energy focus on developing various energy storage solutions for renewable energy sources. Solid Power specializes in solid-state rechargeable batteries for electric vehicles and mobile power applications.

overview_description.description: Antora Energy delivers zero-carbon industrial heat and power to heavy industries that are more reliable than fossil fuels. Antora’s thermal energy storage soaks up excess solar and wind electricity and uses it to heat blocks of carbon so they glow like inside a toaster.

about_short_description.short_description: Antora Energy is electrifying heavy industry with thermal energy storage for zero-carbon heat and power.

product.name: Thermal Battery
product.description: Antora Energy's thermal battery stores renewable electricity as high-temperature heat in carbon blocks, which can be directly used for industrial process heat or converted back to electricity.

product.name: Thermophotovoltaic (TPV) Cells
product.description: Antora Energy produces TPV cells that convert high-temperature heat into electricity, achieving over 40% efficiency.

product.name: TPV Manufacturing Facility
product.description: Antora Energy has established the world's first dedicated manufacturing line for TPV cells, with an initial capacity of 2 MW annually.
